{{2023 Atlantic Coast Conference football standings}}The '''2023 Atlantic Coast Conference football season''', part of the [[2023 NCAA Division I FBS football season]], was the 71st season of [[college football]] play for the [[Atlantic Coast Conference]] (ACC). The ACC consisted of 14 members, with [[2023 California Golden Bears football team|California]], [[2023 Stanford Cardinal football team|Stanford]], and [[2023 SMU Mustangs football team|SMU]] having been announced to join the ACC on July 1, 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-09-01 |title=Cal and Stanford believe move to ACC was needed for survival |url=https://apnews.com/article/cal-stanford-acc-conference-realignment-2259a1439f112679950c48667c2ef5f8 |access-date=2024-12-31 |website=AP News |language=en}}</ref> The 2023 season was the first season without divisions since 2005 (other than the [[2020 Atlantic Coast Conference football season|pandemic-disrupted 2020 season]]). The entire schedule was released on January 30, 2023.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://theacc.com/news/2023/1/30/acc-announces-2023-football-schedule.aspx|title=ACC Announces 2023 Football Schedule|website=TheACC.com|date=January 30, 2023|accessdate=January 30, 2023}}</ref>

