==Coaches==

===Coaching changes===
The ACC entered the 2023 season with two new head football coaches:

* On September 25, 2022, Georgia Tech fired head coach [[Geoff Collins (American football)|Geoff Collins]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=McDaniel |first1=Mike |title=Georgia Tech Fires Coach Geoff Collins, per Reports |date=November 16, 2021|url=https://www.si.com/college/2022/09/25/georgia-tech-fires-coach-geoff-collins-per-report |website=si.com |publisher=Sports Illustrated |access-date=30 January 2023}}</ref> and was replaced by interim head coach [[Brent Key]]. On November 29, 2022, Key was hired as the next head coach.<ref>{{cite web |date=November 29, 2022|title=Virginia Tech names Penn State DC Brent Pry as new head football coach |url=https://ramblinwreck.com/brent-key-named-georgia-tech-footballs-21st-head-coach/ |website=wramblinreck.com |publisher=GT |access-date=20 January 2023}}</ref>
* On December 5, 2022, [[Cincinnati Bearcats football|Cincinnati]] hired Louisville head coach [[Scott Satterfield]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jenkins |first1=Keith |title='I'm honored': Cincinnati Bearcats introduce Scott Satterfield as next head football coach |date=December 5, 2022|url=https://www.cincinnati.com/story/sports/college/university-of-cincinnati/2022/12/05/scott-satterfield-next-football-coach-university-of-cincinnati-bearcats-uc/69700977007/ |website=cincinnati.com |publisher=Cincinnati Enquirer |access-date=30 January 2023}}</ref> and was replaced by former [[Purdue Boilermakers football|Purdue]] head coach [[Jeff Brohm]] on December 7, 2022.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Low |first1=Chris |date=December 7, 2022|title=Sources: Jeff Brohm leaves Purdue, accepts Louisville job |url=https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/35204000/sources-jeff-brohm-leaves-purdue-job-coach-louisville |website=espn.com |publisher=ESPN |access-date=30 January 2023}}</ref>

